# Optional. Local dev uses a built-in mock ORCID (the "mock-orcid" Keycloak
# realm), so you normally need NOTHING here.
#
# Uncomment and fill these ONLY to point the "orcid" broker at a real ORCID
# instead of the mock (e.g. to test the sandbox). Anything left unset falls back
# to the mock. These are the same broker settings a prod Keycloak uses to target
# real ORCID (this file is dev-only; prod runs a separate, external Keycloak).
#
# Register an app at https://sandbox.orcid.org (Developer tools) with redirect URI:
#   http://localhost:8080/realms/igsn/broker/orcid/endpoint
# then copy this file to .env and uncomment:
#
# ORCID_CLIENT_ID=APP-XXXXXXXXXXXX
# ORCID_CLIENT_SECRET=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx
# ORCID_AUTHORIZATION_URL=https://sandbox.orcid.org/oauth/authorize
# ORCID_TOKEN_URL=https://sandbox.orcid.org/oauth/token
# ORCID_USERINFO_URL=https://sandbox.orcid.org/oauth/userinfo
# ORCID_ISSUER=https://sandbox.orcid.org
# ORCID_JWKS_URL=https://sandbox.orcid.org/oauth/jwks
# ORCID_SCOPE=openid
